10/08/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- The remains of five Greek Cypriot prisoners of war missing since 1974 have been found in a mass grave in the village of Tziacs, in northern Cyprus.
The victims, who disappeared after Turkish troops arrived on the island, were identified through DNA tests according to the Investigation Committee on Missing Persons (CMP).
Greek Cypriot CMP member assistant, Xenophon Kallis, said on Sunday (August 9th) that the remains of 14 more victims were found in the same grave but have not yet been identified.
(DPA - 10/08/09;
ANA-MPA - 09/08/09)
